          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The negative pions are produced in the large Chicago",
                "cyclotron by protons of 450 MeV striking a target",
                "which in some of the experiments was copper and in",
                "others beryllium. A sharply collimated beam",
                "containing pions with energy defined within ~3",
                "percent. In addition to the pions this beam contains",
                "some muons and electrons of the same momentum. Their",
                "number has been determined from a range curve. The",
                "muons amount to between 5 percent and 10 percent. The",
                "electrons are present in negligible numbers for beams",
                "above 100 MeV. Below this energy the electron",
                "contamination increases rapidly. For this reason low",
                "energy measurements have been taken by reducing with",
                "a beryllium absorber the energy of the 122-MeV beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A glass cylinder 3 inches in diameter and 7.5 inches",
                "long, closed by 0.005-inch copper windows. This",
                "chamber can be alternately filled with and emptied of",
                "liquid hydrogen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two scintillation crystals of 1-inch-square",
                "cross section separated by a distance of about one",
                "meter. A pair of liquid scintillation counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The coincidences of these two scintillation",
                "counters indicate the number of particles entering",
                "the equipment. Beyond the second crystal the pions",
                "enter the scattering chamber. The particles which are",
                "not scattered out of the beam are recorded by the",
                "coincidences which they give in a pair of liquid",
                "scintillation counters. The double coincidence rate",
                "of the first two scintillators is recorded and at the",
                "same time the quadruple coincidence rate of all four",
                "scintillators. The attenuation of the beam is",
                "obtained from a comparison of the ratio of the",
                "quadruple to double coincidence counts with and",
                "without the hydrogen and is computed as a cross",
                "section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " No details on sources of uncertainties."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A number of corrections have been applied to the",
                "results on account of the following effects:",
                " (1) Background due to accidentals (usually 1 percent",
                "or less).",
                " (2) Angular spread of the beam due to geometry,",
                "diffraction scattering, and pi-mu decay. In some",
                "experiments the multiple scattering was compensated",
                "by means of an equivalent aluminum foil; in others it",
                "was computed. This correction is important only at",
                "low energies.",
                " (3) Muon and electron component in the original beam.",
                "It is assumed that muons and electrons suer only",
                "Coulomb scattering and have no specific nuclear",
                "interaction.",
                " (4) Correction for scattered particles",
                "recorded by the end counters. This correction was",
                "computed on the assumption of isotropic scattering in",
                "the center-of-mass system. It amounted to between 4",
                "percent and 2 percent depending on whether the recoil",
                "protons are or are not recorded. The correction would",
                "be larger if the scattering were predominately",
                "forward but smaller if charge exchange scattering",
                "were important."
              ]
            }
          ],
